<div id="syntax_wiki">
<p>You can use wiki syntax in your message:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>source code bloc</b>: insert the source code between <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;/code&gt;</code></li>
  <li><b>List</b>: each line should begin by one or several <code>*</code>, <code>-</code> or <code>#</code> for numerical list</li>
  <li><b>blockquote</b>:  each line should begin by  one or several <code>&gt;</code></li>
  <li><b>bold</b>: <code>__</code>text<code>__</code> (2 underscores)</li>
  <li><b>italic</b>: <code>''</code>text<code>''</code> (2 quotes)</li>
  <li><b>Link</b>: <code>[</code>link name<code>|</code>link url<code>]</code> or <code>[</code> link url <code>]</code></li>
</ul>
<h4>Advanced wiki syntax</h4>
<ul>
  <li><b>Paragraph</b>: 2 line breaks</li>
  <li><b>Definitions</b>: <code>;</code>term<code> : </code>definition + a line break</li>
</ul>
<p>Inside sentences:</p>
<ul>
  <li><b>Full link</b>: <code>[</code>link name<code>|</code>link url<code>|</code>lang<code>|</code>title<code>]</code></li>
  <li><b>Forced line break</b>: <code>%%%</code></li>
  <li><b>Image</b>: <code>((</code>image link<code>|</code>alternative text<code>|</code>position<code>|</code>description<code>))</code>.
               position: l/L/g/G => left, r/R/d/D =>right, nothing=>inline.</li>
  <li><b>code</b>: <code>@@</code>code<code>@@</code></li>
  <li><b>cite</b>: <code>^^</code>sentence<code>|</code>lang<code>|</code>link of source<code>^^</code></li>
  <li><b>acronym</b>: <code>??</code>acronym<code>|</code>explanation<code>??</code></li>
</ul>
</div>
